title: Ushabti of the Priest Nesi-Kedwet
description:
Pale green faience ushabti of Ns.kdwt. He wears a striated tripartite wig. A bag is incised over left shoulder. The hands are crossed and juxtaposed on chest, right holding a hoe, the left a pick. The back pillar is uninscribed. One line and one column of text in T-shaped pattern read as follows: 
[Hieroglyphs]
Condition: Pale green in color with mottled discoloration.
